headline: Assessing Garmin (GRMN) Valuation After Earnings Beat Guidance Boost And New Product Releases
summary: Garmin (GRMN) just packed several shareholder updates into one day, reporting fourth quarter and full year 2025 results, issuing 2026 revenue guidance, outlining a higher dividend, and confirming fresh product launches. See our latest analysis for Garmin. The strong fourth quarter, new product releases and fresh capital returns appear to have been well received, with a 1-day share price return of 9.44% and a 90-day share price return of 26.92%.
